    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="979"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d979">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14057.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Provisional President told me this afternoon that there was still very much
                    opposition to Villa and that another effort was being made at this time to get
                    him to resign. As Carranza will not resign they expect to eventually drive him
                    out.</p>
                <p>He also said an agreement had been reached with all the troops north of San Luis
                    Potosi to support the Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
